-- German government aims to decide on Opel by mid-week
-- 
-- Mon May 25, 2009 6:46am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/25/us-opel-government-sb-idUSTRE54O1MO20090525

 

 BERLIN  (Reuters) - The German government aims to reach a decision on General Motors' German unit Opel by mid-week, a government spokesman said on Monday. 

 Chancellor Angela Merkel spoke with Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin over the weekend about a possible solution for the German carmaker, the spokesman told reporters. (Reporting by  Kerstin Gehmlich  and  Noah Barkin , Writing by Sarah Marsh)